    "These dynamic laws first must go through a \"filter\", meaning that they first must be evaluated in respect to the fixed laws, making sure that the new transitory regulations do not conflict with the present legal norms.",
    "Within the bounds on the already present legal framework, the regulatory body can then establish new regulations that the industry players need to respect for the time being.",
    "In practice, the regulations that prove to be ineffective will have to be modified, and the ones that prove to become vital for creating adequate rules of the game can then be translated into the body of fixed laws via the much slower democratic processes.The proposed idea has several potential advantages and challenges.",
    "On the upside, it offers a nimble approach to regulation, allowing for quick adaptation to new developments in AI.",
    "The inclusion of industry representatives ensures that the regulations are informed by technical expertise."
